comments.text: @Rhoda-r6j   Luke remains an enigmatic figure, with no independent historical records confirming his existence outside Church tradition. comments.text:
Daniel, as I'm sure you know, the Romans razed Jerusalem, razed the temple, and according to Josephus, killed more than a million Jews in this war around 70 AD. This is what many of the prophecies in the Bible are about. Jesus was absolutely NOT a failed prophet. He talked about this event. 

Though, this doesn't mean all the prophecies in scripture are fulfilled yet. It's important to avoid "full preterism", which is the idea that there isn't even an end of the world and a final judgment. There is clearly a final judgment. 

There are also loads of good answers to all the other objections you raise. Just look for them. For example, Jesus is not denying his divinity when he says "Only God is good", but rebuking the man for thinking his deeds can get him into Heaven, and emphasizing that true goodness comes only from God.
